/-
Result N.7 — G_X-orbit conservation law (the symmetry restatement of A.4).

Reference: `proofs/derived/A4_grade.md` N.7 (A 无条件, A.4 的直接等价表述).

**Statement.** Define the group

    G_X := ⟨ { τ_ω : ω ∈ Ω \ K(X) } ⟩      (composition on Σ*)

generated by token-replacements for knowledge elements *outside* `K(X)`.
Then `X`'s output distribution is invariant under the action of `G_X` on
histories:

    ∀ g ∈ G_X, ∀ h ∈ Σ* :   L(X(h)) = L(X(g · h)) .

**Proof.** A.4 gives invariance for each generator `τ_ω` (`ω ∉ K(X)`).
Any `g ∈ G_X` is a finite composition `τ_{ω₁} ∘ τ_{ω₂} ∘ ⋯`; applying A.4
recursively gives the result.

**Lean kernel.** We represent a finite composition of generators by a
list `ωs : List Ω`, all of whose entries lie outside `K(X)`, acting on a
history `h` via `List.foldr tokenReplace h ωs`.  The base case is `rfl`;
the inductive step is exactly one application of `MIP.Axioms.A4`.  This is
the cleanest A.4 corollary.

**This file is `axiom`-free** apart from the project's foundational
`MIP.Axioms.A4`.
-/
import MIP.Axioms

namespace MIP

namespace OrbitInvariance

open MIP.Axioms

variable {α Ω : Type}

/-- Apply a finite composition of token-replacements `τ_{ω₁}∘⋯∘τ_{ωₙ}` to a
history `h`.  Concretely the right-fold of `tokenReplace` over `ωs`:

    applyReplacements h [ω₁, …, ωₙ] = τ_{ω₁}(τ_{ω₂}(⋯ τ_{ωₙ}(h) ⋯)). -/
def applyReplacements (h : Str α) (ωs : List Ω) : Str α :=
  List.foldr tokenReplace h ωs

@[simp] theorem applyReplacements_nil (h : Str α) :
    applyReplacements h ([] : List Ω) = h := rfl

@[simp] theorem applyReplacements_cons (h : Str α) (ω : Ω) (ωs : List Ω) :
    applyReplacements h (ω :: ωs) = tokenReplace ω (applyReplacements h ωs) := rfl

/-- **N.7 — orbit invariance (list form).**

If every `ω ∈ ωs` lies outside `K(X)`, then applying the corresponding
finite composition of token-replacements to any history `h` leaves `X`'s
output distribution unchanged:

    X h = X (applyReplacements h ωs).

This is the precise content of the `G_X`-invariance: a generic group
element is a finite word in the generators `τ_ω` (`ω ∉ K X`), captured here
by the list `ωs`. -/
theorem orbit_invariance
    (X : Agent α) (h : Str α) (ωs : List Ω)
    (hOut : ∀ ω ∈ ωs, ω ∉ (K X : Set Ω)) :
    X h = X (applyReplacements h ωs) := by
  induction ωs with
  | nil => rfl
  | cons ω rest ih =>
    -- IH: invariance for the tail (all tail tokens are outside K X).
    have hOut_rest : ∀ ω' ∈ rest, ω' ∉ (K X : Set Ω) :=
      fun ω' hω' => hOut ω' (List.mem_cons_of_mem ω hω')
    have hOut_head : ω ∉ (K X : Set Ω) := hOut ω (List.mem_cons_self ..)
    -- X h = X (applyReplacements h rest)            (IH)
    --     = X (τ_ω (applyReplacements h rest))       (A.4 at the head token)
    --     = X (applyReplacements h (ω :: rest))      (definitional)
    calc
      X h = X (applyReplacements h rest) := ih hOut_rest
      _ = X (tokenReplace ω (applyReplacements h rest)) :=
            Axioms.A4 X ω (applyReplacements h rest) hOut_head
      _ = X (applyReplacements h (ω :: rest)) := by
            rw [applyReplacements_cons]

/-- **N.7 — group-action form (consequence).**

Two histories related by a finite composition of out-of-`K(X)`
token-replacements yield equal `X`-output.  Stated as: for any
`g = applyReplacements · ωs` with all `ωs` outside `K X`, the action of
`g` on a history fixes the output distribution.  This is the
`∀ g ∈ G_X` statement once `G_X` is presented by its generators. -/
theorem orbit_invariance_action
    (X : Agent α) (ωs : List Ω)
    (hOut : ∀ ω ∈ ωs, ω ∉ (K X : Set Ω)) :
    ∀ h : Str α, X h = X (applyReplacements h ωs) :=
  fun h => orbit_invariance X h ωs hOut

end OrbitInvariance

end MIP
